00:30:47,112 --> 00:30:50,482
MY NAME IS SAWYER SPARKS.
I'M 22 YEARS OLD.

00:30:50,482 --> 00:30:53,485
I'M FROM BLOOMFIELD, INDIANA,
AND I'M A COLLEGE STUDENT.

00:30:53,485 --> 00:30:55,921
MY FIRST YEAR OF COLLEGE,

00:30:55,921 --> 00:30:58,990
ONE OF MY FAVORITE PROFESSORS
AND HER 5‐YEAR‐OLD CHILD

00:30:58,990 --> 00:31:01,059
MENTIONED THAT THEY HAD
CELIAC DISEASE,

00:31:01,059 --> 00:31:03,161
WHICH MEANS
THEY WERE ALLERGIC TO WHEAT.

00:31:03,161 --> 00:31:04,663
BECAUSE OF THIS ALLERGY,

00:31:04,663 --> 00:31:08,200
HER CHILD COULD NOT PLAY WITH
THE TRADITIONAL MODELING CLAY,

00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,168
LIKE PLAY‐DOH,
THAT WE ALL GREW UP WITH

00:31:10,168 --> 00:31:12,371
BECAUSE THEY ALL CONTAIN WHEAT.

00:31:12,371 --> 00:31:14,840
SO I CREATED SOY‐YER‐DOUGH,
A WHEAT‐FREE, SOY‐BASED

00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:17,342
MODELING CLAY.

00:31:17,342 --> 00:31:19,344
WELCOME TO
THE WORLD HEADQUARTERS

00:31:19,344 --> 00:31:21,580
OF SOY‐YER‐DOUGH
IN MY MOM'S KITCHEN.

00:31:21,580 --> 00:31:24,583
AND THIS IS MY MOM SUE.
SHE DOES ALL THE KNEADING.

00:31:24,583 --> 00:31:27,586
THIS IS MY GIRLFRIEND SAMMIE,
WHO DOES ALL THE MIXING.

00:31:27,586 --> 00:31:30,222
AND I DO ALL THE STIRRING
HERE AT THE STOVE.

00:31:30,222 --> 00:31:32,224
AND WE DO THIS DAY IN
AND DAY OUT,

00:31:32,224 --> 00:31:34,192
EVERY DAY WITH ORDERS.

00:31:34,192 --> 00:31:36,995
THIS BUSINESS
ISN'T JUST ABOUT MAKING MONEY.

00:31:36,995 --> 00:31:39,264
IT'S ABOUT HELPING
ALL THE PEOPLE

00:31:39,264 --> 00:31:41,266
IN THE COMMUNITY
THAT I GREW UP WITH.
CONGRATULATIONS.

00:31:41,266 --> 00:31:44,569
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
YES, THANK YOU.
GLAD TO SEE YOU COME HOME.

00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:47,706
WHAT I REALLY WANT TO DO
IS EXPAND MY BUSINESS,

00:31:47,706 --> 00:31:50,208
OPEN UP A FACTORY
IN BLOOMFIELD, INDIANA,

00:31:50,208 --> 00:31:52,477
AND CREATE JOBS
IN MY COMMUNITY.

00:31:52,477 --> 00:31:55,480
♪♪

00:32:07,959 --> 00:32:10,829
MY NAME IS SAWYER SPARKS,
AND MY PRODUCT IS SOY‐YER‐DOUGH.

00:32:10,829 --> 00:32:14,132
I'M ASKING FOR
A $125,000 INVESTMENT

00:32:14,132 --> 00:32:16,334
FOR 25% OF MY COMPANY.

00:32:16,334 --> 00:32:18,503
THE TRADITIONAL MODELING CLAY

00:32:18,503 --> 00:32:20,505
THAT WE ALL GREW UP WITH
IS WHEAT BASED,

00:32:20,505 --> 00:32:23,308
WHICH CAUSES CHILDREN
WITH AN AVERSION TO WHEAT

00:32:23,308 --> 00:32:26,244
TO FEEL COMPLETELY LEFT OUT.

00:32:26,244 --> 00:32:27,979
SO I INVENTED SOY‐YER‐DOUGH‐‐

00:32:27,979 --> 00:32:29,981
THE FIRST AND ONLY
PATENTED MODELING CLAY

00:32:29,981 --> 00:32:32,017
THAT IS GLUTEN‐FREE,
NONTOXIC AND FUN‐SCENTED.

00:32:32,017 --> 00:32:33,485
OH, IT SMELLS LIKE CHERRY.

00:32:33,485 --> 00:32:35,854
YES, AND IT SMELLS BEST
IF YOU BREAK 'EM APART.

00:32:35,854 --> 00:32:37,856
WHAT PERCENTAGE
OF THE CHILDREN POPULATION

00:32:37,856 --> 00:32:40,158
HAVE THIS PROBLEM?
ACTUALLY, 1 IN 8 CHILDREN.

00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:42,060
OUR COMPETITOR SELLS

00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:45,530
96 MILLION CONTAINERS
OF THIS SIZE A YEAR.

00:32:45,530 --> 00:32:47,532
ONE‐EIGHTH OF THAT IS
12 MILLION CONTAINERS PER YEAR.

00:32:47,532 --> 00:32:50,368
SO THERE'S A HUGE MARKET
FOR THIS.
HOW‐‐HOW MUCH OF THIS
HAVE YOU SOLD SO FAR?

00:32:50,368 --> 00:32:53,071
WE HAVE SOLD 8,000 CONTAINERS
SINCE FEBRUARY.

00:32:53,071 --> 00:32:54,573
UH, THAT'S WHEN THIS BEGAN,

00:32:54,573 --> 00:32:56,741
AND WE JUST LAST WEEK GOT
AN ORDER FOR 11,000 CONTAINERS.

00:32:56,741 --> 00:32:58,643
WOW.

00:32:58,643 --> 00:33:01,346
THE 8,000 YOU SOLD WERE
A RESULT OF YOUR ONLINE SALES?

00:33:01,346 --> 00:33:03,782
ONLINE SALES.
HOW PROPRIETARY
IS THIS PRODUCT?

00:33:03,782 --> 00:33:06,151
IS THERE A PATENT
OF ANY KIND ON IT?

00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:08,587
YES, MINE. IT HAS
A PROVISIONAL PATENT ON IT.

00:33:08,587 --> 00:33:10,222
WHERE ARE YOU
MANUFACTURING THIS?

00:33:10,222 --> 00:33:12,357
OUT OF MY KITCHEN
AT HOME, ACTUALLY.

00:33:12,357 --> 00:33:15,861
H‐HOW ARE YOU DOING THAT?
UH, IT'S MY MOM,
ME AND MY GIRLFRIEND‐‐

00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:17,829
YOU JUST COOK IT YOURSELF?
WE JUST
COOK IT OURSELVES, YES.

00:33:17,829 --> 00:33:21,299
WE CAN ONLY MAKE 12 CONTAINERS,
UH, PER 10 MINUTES.

00:33:21,299 --> 00:33:23,768
HAVE YOU APPROACHED
ANY TOY MAKERS?
WE HAVE AN OFFER‐‐

00:33:23,768 --> 00:33:26,771
HAVE YOU TRIED TO
LICENSE THIS TO PLAY‐DOH?
I HAVE BEEN CONTACTED
BY PLAY‐DOH, THOUGH.

00:33:26,771 --> 00:33:29,107
FOR WHAT?
ABOUT‐‐ABOUT THIS,
TO PURCHASE IT.

00:33:29,107 --> 00:33:31,543
WAIT. WAIT.
AND WHAT HAPPENED?

00:33:31,543 --> 00:33:34,012
AND WHAT DID THEY HAVE TO SAY?
THEY LOVE IT, THEY WANT IT,

00:33:34,012 --> 00:33:36,581
AND WE'RE‐‐
WE'VE BEEN NEGOTIATING

00:33:36,581 --> 00:33:39,484
BECAUSE THEY WANT
THIS PATENT.

00:33:39,484 --> 00:33:43,555
SO THE LARGEST PLAYER
IN THE SPACE CONTACTED YOU...

00:33:43,555 --> 00:33:45,156
MULTIPLE TIMES.
TO LICENSE YOUR PATENT.

00:33:45,156 --> 00:33:46,658
SORRY. MULTIPLE TIMES?
MULTIPLE TIMES.

00:33:46,658 --> 00:33:49,361
AND WHERE IS THAT NEGOTIATION
AT THIS POINT?

00:33:49,361 --> 00:33:52,998
AT THIS POINT, I WANT TO
CREATE JOBS IN MY COMMUNITY‐‐
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT.

00:33:52,998 --> 00:33:55,100
YOU WANT TO SIT
IN YOUR MOTHER'S KITCHEN TABLE

00:33:55,100 --> 00:33:56,568
BAKING THIS STUFF,

00:33:56,568 --> 00:33:59,204
WHEN THE NUMBER ONE GUY
IN THE WORLD IS CALLING YOU?

00:33:59,204 --> 00:34:01,940
ARE YOU NUTS?
NO, HE WANTS
THE WHOLE NEIGHBORHOOD

00:34:01,940 --> 00:34:04,509
TO SIT IN HIS MOTHER'S KITCHEN
BAKING THIS STUFF.
WHY WOULD YOU BAKE
ONE MORE CUP OF THIS STUFF

00:34:04,509 --> 00:34:07,812
WHEN THE NUMBER ONE GUY ON EARTH
IS BANGING AT YOUR DOOR?

00:34:07,812 --> 00:34:09,247
BECAUSE I‐‐

00:34:09,247 --> 00:34:11,249
THIS IS A VERY IMPORTANT MOMENT
FOR YOU,

00:34:11,249 --> 00:34:14,386
'CAUSE IT'S GONNA TELL ME
WHETHER YOU'RE SANE OR INSANE.

00:34:14,386 --> 00:34:15,887
NO, BECAUSE HONESTLY,

00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:18,890
I REALLY FEEL THAT IF THEY
PURCHASE THIS PATENT FROM ME,

00:34:18,890 --> 00:34:21,726
WE WOULD NEVER SEE IT AGAIN
IN THE LIGHT OF DAY.
WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:23,728
(Robert) SAWYER‐‐
MAYBE THAT'S TRUE,
BUT HOW MUCH

00:34:23,728 --> 00:34:26,531
ARE THEY GOING
TO PURCHASE IT FOR?
THAT'S STILL IN NEGOT‐‐
NEGOTIATION.

00:34:26,531 --> 00:34:30,035
IS IT‐‐DO YOU NEED SOME HELP
IN NEGOTIATING THAT?
YEAH.

00:34:30,035 --> 00:34:32,470
HAVE THEY MADE YOU
AN ACTUAL OFFER?

00:34:32,470 --> 00:34:34,773
UH, THROUGH MY LAWYERS,
BUT NOT...
WHAT WAS THEIR PRICE?

00:34:34,773 --> 00:34:36,775
THERE'S BEEN
DIFFERENT OFFERS.

00:34:36,775 --> 00:34:40,111
THE HIGHEST HAS BEEN AROUND
$500,000.

00:34:40,111 --> 00:34:43,782
YOU HAD AN OFFER FOR $500,000?
YOU'RE A COLLEGE STUDENT‐‐

00:34:43,782 --> 00:34:45,784
BUT I REALLY FEEL
THAT IN A YEAR,

00:34:45,784 --> 00:34:47,285
TWO YEARS DOWN THE ROAD,

00:34:47,285 --> 00:34:50,121
I CAN HONESTLY SELL
12 MILLION OF THESE CONTAINERS.

00:34:50,121 --> 00:34:53,024
ARE YOU A WEALTHY GUY,
SAWYER?
NO.

00:34:53,024 --> 00:34:55,760
DIDN'T THE $500,000‐‐I'M JUST
CURIOUS‐‐DIDN'T IT TEMPT YOU?

00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,829
TEMPTED MY PARENTS, YES.
WHAT ABOUT YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

00:34:57,829 --> 00:35:00,498
YES. (laughs)
(laughs)

00:35:00,498 --> 00:35:02,334
WHAT'S YOUR IDEA ABOUT
EMPLOYING PEOPLE?

00:35:02,334 --> 00:35:05,337
I JUST FEEL LIKE I DON'T HAVE MY
FINGER ON YOUR MOTIVATION HERE.

00:35:05,337 --> 00:35:07,339
MY MOTIVATION
IS TO CREATE JOBS,

00:35:07,339 --> 00:35:09,841
TO MAKE SURE THAT THERE'S
A PRODUCT FOR THESE‐‐

00:35:09,841 --> 00:35:11,343
ONE‐EIGHTH OF THE MARKET‐‐

00:35:11,343 --> 00:35:13,745
PLAY‐DOH CAN DO THAT.

00:35:13,745 --> 00:35:15,380
NOT WITH
A WHEAT‐FREE MAR‐‐

00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:17,816
YOU'RE SURE
YOUR PATENT EXCLUDES THEM

00:35:17,816 --> 00:35:20,685
FROM EVER DOING
A WHEAT‐FREE PRODUCT?
YES, YES.

00:35:20,685 --> 00:35:23,054
OUTSTANDING, YOUNG MAN.
OUTSTANDING.

00:35:23,054 --> 00:35:25,657
I RARELY SEE AN OPPORTUNITY LIKE
THIS FROM THE LICENSE FRONT.

00:35:25,657 --> 00:35:28,693
THIS IS
A WONDERFUL OPPORTUNITY.
THANK YOU.

00:35:28,693 --> 00:35:30,462
SAWYER‐‐OH.
SAWYER, I HAVE GREAT NEWS
FOR YOU.

00:35:30,462 --> 00:35:33,565
THANK GOODNESS WE'VE MET.
MY WHOLE BUSINESS CAREER

00:35:33,565 --> 00:35:36,468
WAS BUILT AROUND
LICENSING PROPERTIES.

00:35:36,468 --> 00:35:38,670
DONE IT HUNDREDS OF TIMES.

00:35:38,670 --> 00:35:40,672
I'LL GIVE YOU $125,000
FOR 51% OF YOUR PATENT.

00:35:40,672 --> 00:35:43,575
AND I'LL TELL YOU
WHY I'M DOING THAT.

00:35:43,575 --> 00:35:45,110
I'M DOING IT...

00:35:45,110 --> 00:35:48,913
TO TAKE YOU
OUT OF THE EQUATION.

00:35:48,913 --> 00:35:52,784
AND I PROMISE YOU,
YOU'LL GET A BETTER DEAL

00:35:52,784 --> 00:35:55,920
THAN THE ONE
YOU'RE GETTING RIGHT NOW

00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:58,890
WHEN I SIT DOWN
WITH YOUR FRIENDS AT PLAY‐DOH.

00:35:58,890 --> 00:36:02,694
SAWYER SAID NO TO HALF A MILLION
IN CASH FROM PLAY‐DOH.

00:36:02,694 --> 00:36:05,330
BUT YOU'RE PROPOSING‐‐
HE'S GONNA MAKE MUCH MORE
THAN HALF A MILLION

00:36:05,330 --> 00:36:07,932
WHEN I'M YOUR PARTNER‐‐
MUCH MORE, MUCH MORE.

00:36:07,932 --> 00:36:11,202
BUT YOU'RE TAKING CONTROL.
HE'S‐‐YES,
BECAUSE I SHOULD SIT‐‐

00:36:11,202 --> 00:36:14,039
SO YOU COULD SELL IT
FOR $600,000.
I DON'T‐‐

00:36:14,039 --> 00:36:17,208
THERE'S NOTHING HE CAN DO.
ROBERT, YOU'RE JUST
MAKING NOISE TO ME.

00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:19,878
LOOK, KEVIN‐‐
SAWYER, LET ME SWEETEN MY OFFER,
'CAUSE THIS IS NOISE.

00:36:19,878 --> 00:36:22,881
I'M TIRED OF LISTENING TO IT.
HERE'S A BETTER DEAL FOR YOU.

00:36:22,881 --> 00:36:26,384
WE'LL KEEP IT THIS WAY‐‐
51% AT $125,000,

00:36:26,384 --> 00:36:29,854
AND YOU DON'T HAVE TO CLOSE
UNTIL I FINISH THE NEGOTIATIONS

00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:31,489
WITH THESE GUYS.

00:36:31,489 --> 00:36:34,426
IF YOU DON'T LIKE THE DEAL,
WALK AWAY.

00:36:34,426 --> 00:36:37,128
I'M GONNA BE
YOUR ADVOCATE RIGHT NOW,

00:36:37,128 --> 00:36:40,265
BECAUSE I KNOW ABOUT LICENSING,
BUT HONESTLY,

00:36:40,265 --> 00:36:43,168
I THINK HE IS GIVING YOU
AN INCREDIBLE DEAL.

00:36:43,168 --> 00:36:46,571
I'D CONSIDER THIS
WHAT WE CALL A "YOLO" MOMENT.

00:36:46,571 --> 00:36:49,674
YOU ONLY LIVE ONCE.

00:36:49,674 --> 00:36:51,943
ALL RIGHT?
YES.

00:36:51,943 --> 00:36:53,945
AND TO MAKE SURE
THAT I DON'T COMPETE,

00:36:53,945 --> 00:36:56,214
'CAUSE I THINK THAT IS
A REALLY GOOD DEAL...

00:36:56,214 --> 00:36:59,117
I'M OUT.

00:36:59,117 --> 00:37:01,753
I'M GONNA GET RID
OF THE CLUTTER.

00:37:01,753 --> 00:37:04,389
UM, I THINK A SPECIALIST
IN LICENSING

00:37:04,389 --> 00:37:07,292
LIKE KEVIN O'LEARY IS‐‐
IS A GOOD PARTNER TO HAVE,

00:37:07,292 --> 00:37:09,294
SO I‐‐I'M GONNA BOW OUT.

00:37:09,294 --> 00:37:11,362
OKAY.
HE'S THE NATURAL PARTNER
FOR YOU,

00:37:11,362 --> 00:37:14,332
AND I DON'T EVEN LIKE THE GUY,
SO FOR ME TO ENDORSE HIM

00:37:14,332 --> 00:37:16,334
IS SHOCKING TO MYSELF.
I'M OUT.

00:37:18,103 --> 00:37:21,106
SO YOU JUST WANT TO RAISE
SOME CASH TO DO WHAT?

00:37:21,106 --> 00:37:24,442
UH, TO BUILD A FACILITY
IN MY COMMUNITY.

00:37:24,442 --> 00:37:26,444
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,
MY FRIEND,

00:37:26,444 --> 00:37:28,947
I'VE BEEN RICH
AND I'VE BEEN POOR.

00:37:28,947 --> 00:37:32,050
RICH IS MUCH BETTER,
AND I WANT TO GET YOU THERE.

00:37:32,050 --> 00:37:34,285
YOU'LL FIND MANY WAYS
TO CREATE JOBS

00:37:34,285 --> 00:37:36,888
WHEN YOU HAVE THE CAPITAL
TO BUILD BUSINESS.

00:37:36,888 --> 00:37:39,791
COULD I ASK YOU A QUESTION?
YES.

00:37:39,791 --> 00:37:42,861
HOW MUCH DO YOU LOVE MONEY?
DO YOU LOVE IT AS MUCH AS I DO?
PROBABLY NOT.

00:37:42,861 --> 00:37:44,863
I'M STILL IN COL‐‐
I'M A COLLEGE STUDENT AND...

00:37:44,863 --> 00:37:47,665
(laughs)
I JUST NEED MONEY
FOR BEER, I GUESS,

00:37:47,665 --> 00:37:50,268
IS WHAT THIS IS.
(sharks laugh)

00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:52,337
(O'Leary)
THIS IS SUCH WHAT I DO.

00:37:52,337 --> 00:37:55,073
THIS IS IN MY BLOOD,
WHAT YOU'RE DOING HERE.

00:37:55,073 --> 00:37:57,075
THERE'S NO PERSON
BETTER ON EARTH

00:37:57,075 --> 00:38:00,044
TO BE IN YOUR SHOES THAN ME.

00:38:00,044 --> 00:38:02,914
BELIEVE ME. WE NEED TO BE
PARTNERS ON THIS.

00:38:02,914 --> 00:38:05,617
ARE WE GONNA BE IN BUSINESS
OR NOT?

00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:07,619
I LOVE YOUR OFFER.

00:38:07,619 --> 00:38:10,121
AND I DEFINITELY FEEL
THAT I DO NEED HELP,

00:38:10,121 --> 00:38:12,624
UH, WITH THIS, AND, UH,

00:38:12,624 --> 00:38:15,026
BUT NOT FOR 51%.

00:38:15,026 --> 00:38:16,528
♪♪

00:38:16,528 --> 00:38:21,533
COULD YOU DO $125,000
FOR 40%?

00:38:21,533 --> 00:38:23,001
HERE'S THE PROBLEM‐‐

