IS, WHEN I BEGIN NEGOTIATIONS,

00:38:32,644 --> 00:38:34,979
THE OTHER SIDE HAS TO KNOW

00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:36,981
THAT I HAVE
THE ABILITY TO CLOSE.

00:38:36,981 --> 00:38:40,084
BUT I COULD STILL GIVE YOU
THE ABILITY TO CLOSE ON‐‐

00:38:40,084 --> 00:38:42,487
NO. YOU SEE,
HAVING NEGOTIATED THIS LICENSE

00:38:42,487 --> 00:38:44,489
HUNDREDS OF TIMES BEFORE,

00:38:44,489 --> 00:38:46,357
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO TRUST ME.

00:38:46,357 --> 00:38:49,561
I WOULD NEVER, EVER DO THIS
WITHOUT HAVING THE ABILITY

00:38:49,561 --> 00:38:52,564
TO GO IN THERE
AND COME BACK WITH A DEAL

00:38:52,564 --> 00:38:54,065
THAT'S SIGNIFICANTLY SUPERIOR.

00:38:54,065 --> 00:38:56,367
IF YOU TELL ME
ONE OF THE ATTRIBUTES

00:38:56,367 --> 00:38:59,370
IS YOU HAVE TO CREATE JOBS,
I'LL GET THAT FOR YOU.

00:38:59,370 --> 00:39:02,273
I AM WILLING TO BEND OVER
BACKWARDS TO GET YOU HAPPY

00:39:02,273 --> 00:39:04,275
IN THE STRUCTURE OF THE DEAL,

00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:06,811
BUT I HAVE TO WALK IN THERE
WITH 51%,

00:39:06,811 --> 00:39:09,247
AND I SWEAR,
I'LL COME OUT OF THERE

00:39:09,247 --> 00:39:11,883
WITH SOMETHING
YOU CAN'T EVEN DREAM OF.
SAWYER, IT'S A GREAT SPEECH...

00:39:11,883 --> 00:39:13,885
AND IT'S TRUE.
AND YOU KNOW WHAT, SAWYER?

00:39:13,885 --> 00:39:16,387
I ALMOST BELIEVED
IT FOR A SECOND.

00:39:16,387 --> 00:39:18,389
BUT I THINK YOU DID
AN EXCELLENT JOB TODAY

00:39:18,389 --> 00:39:20,758
OF SEEING THROUGH
THE FLUFFINESS

00:39:20,758 --> 00:39:22,760
AND INTO WHAT IT REALLY IS,
JUST GREED.

00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:27,298
I'LL GIVE YOU THE $125,000
FOR THE 40%.

00:39:27,298 --> 00:39:31,436
SO WE'RE‐‐WE'RE‐‐
(whimpers) I'M GONNA CRY.
I CAN'T TAKE IT.

